x4freetext: 1.25 Gramm/Cm**2 Lead Target.
Two Position-Sensitive Plastic Scintillators
Located in the Intermediate and in the Final Focal
Planes, Respectively, Provide the Time-Of-Flight and
Magnetic Rigidity Measurements.

x4codes.hlp: GSI Helmholtzzent. f. Schwerionenforschung, Darmstadt, Germany

x4freetext: Heavy-Ion Synchrotron.

x4codes.hlp: GSI Helmholtzzent. f. Schwerionenforschung, Darmstadt, Germany

x4freetext: Fragment Separator.
The Identification in Mass and Charge is Based
On the Measurements of the Magnetic Rigidity, Time of
Flight and Energy Loss For Each Fragment Passing
Through the Fragment Separator.

x4codes.hlp: Off-line mass separation of a product
On-line mass separation of a product

x4freetext: - By Authors - The Magnetic Selection and the
Kinematical Analysis of the Measured Isotopes Allowed
To Disentangle Fission and the Fragmentation Residues.
While Fragmentation (SPALLATION) Residues have
Velocities Close to That of the Beam, the Velocity
Vectors of Fission Products Populate a Narrow Shell of
A Large Sphere in the Frame Moving with Beam Velocity.
After Conversion Into the Laboratory Frame, the
Velocity Distribution of the Fission Residues Populates
The Surface of an Ellipsoid, While
Spallation-Evaporation Reactions Populate the Center of
This Ellipsoid.
Corrected Data from Internet Site are
Included
Last checking has been done.
From Web-Site of the Laboratory.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: No any Information.
1. Main Correction is Due to the Transmission of the
Fragments Through the Separator. The Transmission was
Estimated by Ion-Optical Calculations.
2. Correction For Dead Time of Data Acquisition Which
Varied from 5% to 20%, Depending on the Counting Rate.
3. Losses of Fragments by Secondary Reactions in the
Target and the Intermediate-Focus Plastic Scintillator
Are Corrected For.
4. All Fragments were Fully Stripped and Contributions
From Other Ionic Charge States were Negligible.
The Results were Compared with Empirical Formula
(EPAX).
Effective Proton Evaporation Barrier was Determined.
